{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":103868,"duration_api_ms":103806,"num_turns":26,"result":"","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"7066a518-e887-4263-9bac-1738c3da43ee","total_cost_usd":0.9082674999999999,"usage":{"input_tokens":17,"cache_creation_input_tokens":68380,"cache_read_input_tokens":743865,"output_tokens":4355,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":68380,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6":{"inputTokens":17,"outputTokens":4355,"cacheReadInputTokens":743865,"cacheCreationInputTokens":68380,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.9082674999999999,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"structured_output":{"amendments":[{"body":"BUG: In `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:4634-4636`, the pre-backoff snapshot code sets `snapshot.active_run = None` before sleeping. After the sleep, the loop continues back to line 4473, which calls `carry_forward_active_run(snapshot, ...)`. This function calls `current_active_run(snapshot)` (line 590), which requires `snapshot.active_run.is_some()` and returns `Err(AppError::CorruptRecord)` when it's `None`. Every retry with non-zero backoff will immediately fail with a CorruptRecord error, making the backoff feature worse than useless — it converts a retryable failure into a fatal one. Fix: after the sleep (and before `continue`), restore `snapshot.active_run` from `snapshot.interrupted_run` (which was saved by `preserve_interrupted_run` at line 4634) and reset `snapshot.status = RunStatus::Running`.","rationale":"This is the core bug in the change set. The pre-backoff snapshot persistence for crash resilience is a sound idea, but the snapshot must be restored to a usable state before the retry loop iteration continues. Without this fix, the entire retry hardening feature is broken — any stage failure that triggers a non-zero backoff (which is all of them by default) will immediately fail with CorruptRecord on the next iteration."},{"body":"Missing test coverage for the backoff snapshot round-trip. The new backoff snapshot code at `engine.rs:4622-4664` is a critical path (it's the only code path that sets `active_run = None` mid-retry-loop) but has no integration or unit test. Add a test that exercises a stage failure with backoff enabled, verifying that: (1) the snapshot written during backoff has `status = Failed` and `active_run = None`, (2) after the backoff sleep, the retry loop successfully restores state and re-enters the stage, and (3) if the process is killed during backoff, `run resume` can recover from the persisted snapshot.","rationale":"The CorruptRecord bug above would have been caught by even a basic test. Given this is a crash-resilience path with subtle state transitions, test coverage is essential to prevent regressions."}],"summary":"Reviewed the diff (3 files changed: retry policy updates in retry_policy.rs, saturating_add fix in service.rs, and backoff snapshot persistence in engine.rs). Found one critical bug and one significant test gap. The retry_policy.rs changes (increased limits, BinaryNotFound terminal, exponential backoff) are correct. The service.rs saturating_add change is a safe improvement. However, the backoff snapshot code in engine.rs has a fatal bug: it sets `snapshot.active_run = None` for crash-resilience persistence but never restores it before the next loop iteration, causing every backoff retry to fail with `CorruptRecord`. The process_backend.rs timeout enforcement and exit code classification (already present in the codebase, not part of this diff) look correct — timeout is enforced via `tokio::time::timeout` around `io_and_wait`, and exit 127 maps to BinaryNotFound."},"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"a4d1a4b8-37ed-4292-8b66-d1524d15cfe2"}
